SIMPLE: filioque
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Filioque
<hw>Fil`i*o"que</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl.
Hist.)</fld> <def>The Latin for, ⟦ldquo⟧and from the Son,⟦rdquo⟧
equivalent to <xex>et filio</xex>, inserted by the third council of
Toledo (<sc>a. d.</sc> 589) in the clause <xex>qui ex Patre
procedit</xex> (who proceedeth from the Father) of the
Niceno-Constantinopolitan Creed (<sc>a. d.</sc> 381), which makes a
creed state that the Holy Ghost proceeds from the Son as well as from
the Father. Hence, the doctrine itself (not admitted by the Eastern
Church).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Filipendulous</ent>⟦br⟧
